        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "Fix MiniMax token plan display",
        "body": "## Summary\n- keep fetching MiniMax remains JSON when coding-plan HTML only yields a coarse Prompts fallback\n- accept MiniMax current alternate `*_boost_permille` fields in addition to the existing `*_boost_permill` spelling\n- preserve critical fallback semantics: cancellation, cancelled URL errors, invalid credentials, and endpoint override errors are rethrown instead of hidden behind coarse HTML data\n- carry the parsed HTML plan name onto remains-enriched snapshots when group metadata is unavailable\n- add regression coverage for the current TokenPlanPlus response shape, boosted weekly quota display, plan-name preservation, auth failure, and cancellation\n\n## Redacted MiniMax proof\nRan the current PR build locally against the configured MiniMax provider using `codexbar diagnose`. Raw token/cookie/account data is not emitted by diagnose; private plan and quota values are additionally redacted here before posting publicly. The live output confirms the fixed path returns two MiniMax quota lanes instead of the old coarse Prompts fallback:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"provider\": \"minimax\",\n  \"source\": \"api\",\n  \"settings\": { \"apiRegion\": \"cn\", \"sourceMode\": \"auto\" },\n  \"details\": {\n    \"minimax\": {\n      \"planName\": \"<redacted>\",\n      \"services\": [\n        { \"displayName\": \"General\", \"windowType\": \"5 hours\", \"usage\": \"<redacted>\", \"limit\": \"<redacted>\", \"remaining\": \"<redacted>\", \"percent\": \"<redacted>\" },\n        { \"displayName\": \"General\", \"windowType\": \"Weekly\", \"usage\": \"<redacted>\", \"limit\": \"<redacted>\", \"remaining\": \"<redacted>\", \"percent\": \"<redacted>\" }\n      ]\n    }\n  },\n  \"usage\": {\n    \"windows\": [\n      { \"label\": \"primary\", \"windowMinutes\": 300 },\n      { \"label\": \"secondary\", \"windowMinutes\": 10080 }\n    ]\n  }\n}\n```\n\nI also launched the locally packaged PR app (`CodexBar.app 0.37.1 (91)`) and verified the MiniMax menu renders the token-plan name plus separate `General · 5h` and `General · Weekly` quota rows. Private quota values are not posted publicly.\n\n## Test\n- `CLANG_MODULE_CACHE_PATH=.build/module-cache swift test --filter MiniMax`\n- `./Scripts/lint.sh lint-macos`\n- `./Scripts/lint.sh lint-linux`",
